    • Method Detail

      • start

        protected Bell start()
        Description copied from class: Transfer
        Called when this Transfer is started. This method may return a Bell which will ring when the Transfer is ready, or null to indicate that it is ready immediately.

        Exceptions thrown here or through the returned Bell will cause the Transfer to be stopped.

        No other transfer methods will be called until this method has completed and the returned Bell, if non-null, has rung. This method will be called at most once.

        Overrides:
        start in class Transfer<S extends Resource<?,S>,D extends Resource<?,D>>
        Returns:
        A Bell which will ring when the Transfer has started, or null if it is ready immediately.

      • stop

        protected void stop()
        Description copied from class: Transfer
        This is called when the Transfer has been terminated. Once stopped, the transfer cannot be started again. This may be called before Transfer.start() if the transfer is canceled before it starts.
        Overrides:
